  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I want to build `status-react` when the computer is not online or having a poor internet connection.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nDuring ETHDenver hackathon I needed to build a custom version of `status-react`. WiFi connection was dead there, and that became a complete blocker for building `status-react`. The error I've got was similar to this (it's an output from the build script `./scripts/build_android.sh` without an internet connection at all):\r\n\r\n```\r\nFAILURE: Build failed with an exception.\r\n\r\n* What went wrong:\r\nA problem occurred configuring project ':react-native-vector-icons'.\r\n> Could not resolve all files for configuration ':react-native-vector-icons:classpath'.\r\n   > Could not resolve com.android.tools.build:gradle:2.3.+.\r\n     Required by:\r\n         project :react-native-vector-icons\r\n      > Could not resolve com.android.tools.build:gradle:2.3.+.\r\n         > Failed to list versions for com.android.tools.build:gradle.\r\n            > Unable to load Maven meta-data from https://jcenter.bintray.com/com/android/tools/build/gradle/maven-metadata.xml.\r\n               > Could not HEAD 'https://jcenter.bintray.com/com/android/tools/build/gradle/maven-metadata.xml'.\r\n                  > jcenter.bintray.com: nodename nor servname provided, or not known\r\n\r\n* Try:\r\nRun with --stacktrace option to get the stack trace. Run with --info or --debug option to get more log output.\r\n\r\n* Get more help at https://help.gradle.org\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm pretty sure that `status-react` can be perfectly built without building tools trying to update something. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n`status-react` builds.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nIt fails trying to resolve some hostnames.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n - disable wifi connection on your laptop\r\n - run `./scripts/build-android.sh` script",
